`app.listen(3000)` binds to `0.0.0.0` by default and serves plaintext. In production you'd normally terminate TLS at a load balancer, but the app should still:

- Bind to the interface you actually want (`app.listen(port, '127.0.0.1', ...)` when fronted by a local proxy).
