The code is small and has no obvious injection sinks (no SQL, no `eval`, no shell exec, no user-controlled file paths, no template rendering). However, it's missing almost every baseline hardening control you'd want before running this in production. Below is a prioritized list of findings mapped to OWASP Top 10.

