app.use(cors({
  origin: (origin, cb) => {
    const allow = (process.env.ALLOWED_ORIGINS || '').split(',').filter(Boolean);
    if (!origin || allow.includes(origin)) return cb(null, true);
    return cb(new Error('origin not allowed'));
  },
  credentials: false,
  methods: ['GET'],
  maxAge: 600,
}));
```

---

### 🟠 MEDIUM — M3: No Body-Size / Parser Hardening (`A05`)

Not yet exploited because there's no body parser, but once you add `app.use(express.json())` it defaults to 100 KB and accepts `Content-Type: application/json` only if the body is valid JSON. Set explicit, small limits to prevent memory abuse:

